        "content": "<p>If I've defined a cohort of patients in a List or Group, is there a way to get a list of encounters, observations, etc. for that cohort using a FHIR query?</p>",
        "id": 153821533,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Grenz",
        "timestamp": 1460568350
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>_list doesn't seem to support...</p>",
        "id": 153821534,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Grenz",
        "timestamp": 1460568370
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Interesting idea.  Sort of similar to the \"in\" relationship for value sets.  We'd need to define what types of resources could be used and how to find the \"members\" to evaluate against.  CareTeam would be another possibility</p>",
        "id": 153821561,
        "sender_full_name": "Lloyd McKenzie",
        "timestamp": 1460575986
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right - I was thinking a modifier on the reference search type.  Encounter?patient:in=List/42</p>",
        "id": 153821562,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Grenz",
        "timestamp": 1460576039
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Feel free to submit a change request :)</p>",
        "id": 153821563,
        "sender_full_name": "Lloyd McKenzie",
        "timestamp": 1460576108
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"191316\">@Grahame Grieve</span> was talking about metadata needed for search.  This kind of thing highlights that need...</p>",
        "id": 153821564,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Grenz",
        "timestamp": 1460576126
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Will do.</p>",
        "id": 153821565,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Grenz",
        "timestamp": 1460576131
